    "As Nobel laureate Herbert Simon first noted over 40 years ago, a wealth of information makes attention a scarce resource (Simon, 1971).",
    "Since then, the rise of the internet, big data, and artificial intelligence (AI) has not only drastically increased the amount of information available to us, it's also fundamentally transformed how information is produced, distributed, and consumed.",
    "This technological revolution has therefore had a transformative effect on the attention economy.",
    "1 Among the most notable features of the digital attention economy is the way online platforms filter and rank information according to individual users' preferences, among other factors.",
    "This process centrally involves algorithmic recommender systems."
  ],
